description.p:
The present disclosure provides to a continuous round baler comprising: a first bale chamber and a second bale chamber operably coupled by a conveyor system; wherein the first bale chamber is positioned at a front of the baler and the second bale chamber is positioned at a rear of the baler, wherein each of the first and second bale chambers comprise a first sidewall and a second sidewall, an entry point at the front of the first and second bale chambers, an outlet at a rear of the first and second bale chambers, and at least one floor roller positioned at a bottom of each of the bale chambers transverse to the first and second sidewalls; wherein the conveyor system is positioned between the first and second bale chambers at a downward angle from the front of the baler to the rear of the baler;

a crop harvesting assembly positioned in front of the baler and operably connected to the first bale chamber;

a first serpentine system arranged for the first bale chamber, the first serpentine system comprising:

a first bale carrier positioned at the outlet of the first bale chamber; and
a plurality of baling belt rollers in operable contact with one or more baling belts, the plurality of baling belt rollers comprising two lower baling belt rollers movable in an up and downward direction independent of movement of any other baling belt rollers in the baler;
a second serpentine system arranged for the second bale chamber, the second serpentine system comprising:

a second bale carrier positioned at the entry point of the second bale chamber;
a third bale carrier positioned at the outlet of the second bale chamber; and
a plurality of baling belt rollers in operable contact with one or more baling belts, the plurality of baling belt rollers comprising two belt rollers movable in the fore and aft directions and independent of movement of any other rollers in the baler; wherein the second and third bale carriers are in operable contact with the one or more baling belts.
The downward angle of the conveyor system allows for bale transfer between the first and second bale chambers to be achieved more easily by movement of the conveyor system combined with the downward force of gravity.

In some embodiments, the present disclosure provides to a continuous round baler comprising: a first bale chamber and a second bale chamber operably coupled by a conveyor system; wherein the first bale chamber is positioned at a front of the baler and the second bale chamber is positioned at a rear of the baler, wherein each of the first and second bale chambers comprise a first sidewall and a second sidewall, an entry point at the front of the first and second bale chambers, an outlet at a rear of the first and second bale chambers, and at least one floor roller positioned at a bottom of each of the bale chambers transverse to the first and second sidewalls; wherein the conveyor system is positioned between the first and second bale chambers at a downward angle from the front of the baler to the rear of the baler;

a crop harvesting assembly positioned in front of the baler and operably connected to the first bale chamber;

a first serpentine system arranged for the first bale chamber, the first serpentine system comprising:

a first bale carrier positioned at the outlet of the first bale chamber; and
a plurality of baling belt rollers in operable contact with one or more baling belts, the plurality of baling belt rollers comprising two lower baling belt rollers movable in an up and downward direction independent of movement of any other baling belt rollers in the baler;
a second serpentine system arranged for the second bale chamber, the second serpentine system comprising:

a second bale carrier positioned at the entry point of the second bale chamber;
a third bale carrier positioned at the outlet of the second bale chamber; and
a plurality of baling belt rollers in operable contact with one or more baling belts, the plurality of baling belt rollers comprising two belt rollers movable in the fore and aft directions and independent of movement of any other rollers in the baler; wherein the second and third bale carriers are in operable contact with the one or more baling belts; and wherein each of the first, second, and third bale carriers are movable in the upward and downward directions by a mechanical device operatively coupled to the first pair of arms and/or the second pair of arms of each of the first, second, and third bale carriers; and wherein the second bale carrier forms a front side of a bale in the second bale chamber in its fully closed position, wraps the fully formed bale while in transition to its closed position and receives a partially formed bales from the first bale chamber in an open position; and wherein the third bale forms a rear side of the bale in the second bale chamber in its fully closed position and facilitates evacuation of the bale in an open position.

claim.claim-text:
A harvester comprising:
a first bale chamber (310) and a second bale chamber (320) operably coupled by a conveyor system (330);
wherein the first bale chamber (310) is positioned at one end of the harvester and the second bale chamber (320) is positioned at the opposite end of the harvester;
wherein each of the first (310) and second bale chambers (320) comprise:
a first sidewall and a second sidewall,
an entry point at one end of the first and second bale chambers (310, 320),
an outlet at the opposite end of the first (310) and second bale chambers (320), and
at least one floor roller (311) positioned at the bottom of each of the bale chambers transverse to the first and second sidewalls;
wherein the conveyor system (330) is positioned between the first (310) and second bale chambers (320) and comprises one or a plurality of endless belts (334) extending around and supported by at least one stationary roller (333) and at least a first movable roller (331);
wherein the at least one stationary roller (333) and the at least first movable roller (331) are positioned transverse to the first and second sidewalls and spin about a rotational axis; and
wherein the rotational axis of the at least first moveable roller (331) is capable of movement in one or more operable positions independent of the rotational axis of the at least one stationary roller (333) such that the position of the at least first movable roller (331) creates more than two points of inflection in the one or plurality of endless belts (334).

The harvester of any of the claims 1-5 further comprising:
a harvesting assembly (303) positioned on one end of the harvester and operably connected to the first bale chamber (310);
a first serpentine system (340) arranged for the first bale chamber (310), the first serpentine system (340) comprising:
a first bale carrier (350) positioned at the outlet of the first bale chamber (310); and
a plurality of baling belt rollers in operable contact with one or more baling belts (341), the plurality of baling belt rollers comprising two lower baling belt rollers (391, 392) movable in an upward and downward direction independent of movement of any other baling belt rollers in the first serpentine system (340);
a second serpentine system (360) arranged for the second bale chamber (320), the second serpentine system (360) comprising:
a second bale carrier (370) positioned at the entry point of the second bale chamber (320);
a third bale carrier (380) positioned at the outlet of the second bale chamber (320); and
a plurality of baling belt rollers in operable contact with one or more baling belts, the plurality of baling belt rollers independently movable from any other roller in the second serpentine system (360); and
a net wrapping mechanism (390) in or proximate to the second bale chamber (320) optionally positioned under the third bale carrier (380) or above the second bale carrier (370) in the front of the second bale chamber (320);
wherein the second (370) and third (380) bale carriers are in operable contact with the one or more baling belts.

The harvester of claim 6, wherein the first (350), second (370), and third (380) bale carriers are movable among a closed position and one or more open positions, the second (370) and third (380) bale carriers comprising:
a first pair of arms (375; 385) extending transversely from and affixed to a first pair of pivot points (373; 383) on the first and second sidewalls;
a second pair of arms (376; 386) extending transversely from and affixed to a second pair of pivot points (374; 384) on the first and second sidewalls;
one or more fixed members (372; 382) positioned at a distance defined by the length of the first and second pair of arms.

The harvester of any of the claims 6-11, wherein the harvester comprises at least a first, second, third and fourth operable conditions, wherein

the first operable condition comprises the first bale carrier (350) in a fully closed position, the third bale carrier (380) in a fully closed position and the first movable roller (331) of the conveyor system (330) in a maximally forward position, wherein the harvesting assembly (302) facilitates movement of harvested material (301) into the first bale chamber (310), wherein the first bale carrier (350) in a fully closed position and the first movable roller (331) in a maximally forward position facilitates formation of harvested material (301) into a bale of a predetermined size, wherein the fully closed position of the third bale carrier (380) optionally allows a wholly separate bale to exist in the second bale chamber (320) prior to evacuation of the wholly separate bale from the harvester;

the second operable condition comprises the first bale carrier (350) and the second bale carrier (370) in a fully raised position, and the first movable roller (331) of the conveyor system (330) in a rearward position relative to its maximally forward position, wherein the fully raised positions of the first (350) and second bale carriers (370) and the rearward position of the first movable roller (331) allows for exit of the bale from the first bale chamber (310) to the second bale chamber (320); wherein the rotational axis of the first movable roller (331) is moving to facilitate the transfer of the bale from the first to the second bale chamber (320);

the third operable condition comprises the second and the third bale carrier (380)s in a fully closed position, and the first movable roller (331) of the conveyor system (330) in a maximally rearward position, wherein the fully closed positions of the second (370) and third (380) bale carriers and the maximally rearward position of the first movable roller (331) allows for crop to be transferred from the harvesting assembly, through the first bale chamber (310) and into the second bale chamber (320);

the fourth operable condition comprises the first bale carrier (350) and second bale carrier (370) in a fully closed position, the third bale carrier (380) in a fully raised position, and the first movable roller (331) of the conveyor system (330) in a position forward of its position in the third operable condition, wherein the fully raised position of the third bale carrier (380) allows evacuation of the bale from the harvester.

A method of harvesting material (301) in the harvester of any of the claims 1-14, said method comprising:
(a) feeding material (301) from a harvesting assembly into the first bale chamber (310);
(b) forming a partially formed bale in the first bale chamber (310) to a desired size;
(c) transferring the partially formed bale from the first bale chamber (310) to the second bale chamber (320) on the conveyor system (330);
(d) completing bale formation in the second bale chamber (320); and
(e) ejecting the completed bale from the second bale chamber (320) contemporaneously with initiating step (a) in a new sequence of steps (a) through (d).
